HEADWORD: Burnisher
<hw>Bur"nish*er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who burnishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tool with a hard, smooth, rounded end or surface,
as of steel, ivory, or agate, used in smoothing or polishing by rubbing.
It has a variety of forms adapted to special uses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burnous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Burnoose</ent>⟦br⟧
